SIMPLE: boondoggle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: boondoggle
<hw>boon"dog*gle</hw> <pos>v.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a braided cord made
by hand by young scouts, used for various purposes, such as a hat cord
or a key chain.</def></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a useless, wasteful, or impractical project; --
especially one authorized by a government agency as a favor to
partisans, to employ unemployed people, or in return for corrupt
payments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>boondoggle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: boondoggle
<hw>boon"dog*gle</hw> <pos>v.</pos> <def>to do useless, wasteful, or
trivial work.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boor</ent>⟦br⟧
